content: The Team World Championship offered so many exciting theories and new ideas.
So there is a lot to analyse and discuss.
Now, all the 144 TWC games have been published in www.renju.net website,
all the errors have been fixed, and missing games added, compared to lib files in forum.
These 11 moves - a very exciting theory in 2006.
I have seen so many games played in this variants already, maybe about 20.
Sometimes black player won, sometimes white.
But as it happens to all new variants, sooner or later the analysts find the optimal plan,
and sometimes it may even result with sure win for one side.
There have been 3 kinds of white ideas here.
One is purely defensive, such as 12-L10,
but the tournament results show that in those cases black always won.
Then there is a semi-active tactics,
Black cannot make their strongest move - k8, because of 3x3
But the games in TWC proved that black wins here anyway.
Now, there is no defense at all.
So, the only chance for white is to be active.
The first games of this appeared in last year already.
At first, it was used by white players of gambling style, who only counted on 3x3 trap at h12.
Then, for nearly half a year, the move 15-f8 raised questions.
Chen Wei had an unlucky game with Timo Ilu,
where he pushed the h12 3x3 without success.
And Timo won it without fight.
Before TWC, this 16th move was considered to be good for white.
Black could only survive with long series of "only" moves.
white is also doing its best moves since 16th.
With move 41, black still could not get the tempo
and the 43-f12 is likely the best one among all defense moves.
After that white gets the attack chance below.
But, with proper defense moves black can defend here quite soon,
and then the game goes to left upper side with black small advantage.

So, if the variant ends with draw, or black advantage,
then the 16th move may not be the best solution.
During TWC, all the teams analysed this variant carefully.
A day before the finals, Tunnet offered this 16th move to our team members,
in order to use it against Russia in final.
And to use this 24th, to start up the powerful white plan.
Together, we quickly checked all other 17th moves,

yeah, Zhu said, this is white win.

So lets analyse the Chinese team's solution together.
